&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>How to get started with chaos engineering (k6 Office Hours)</title><link>https://nicolevanderhoeven.github.io/blog/20210430-koh-pokemon/</link><pubDate>Fri, 30 Apr 2021 21:53:09 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://nicolevanderhoeven.github.io/blog/20210430-koh-pokemon/</guid><description>&lt;p>Recently, I&amp;rsquo;ve been learning more about chaos engineering. In this week&amp;rsquo;s k6 Office Hours, I shared my experience as a tester getting started with Kubernetes, chaos engineering with &lt;a href="https://github.com/simskij/xk6-chaos">xk6-chaos&lt;/a> and k6, and observability with &lt;a href="https://newrelic.com">New Relic&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
